{"questionId":"22146755","questionHtml":"<p>Solve&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>9</mn><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognising a quadratic in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mfenced><msup><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></msup></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>valid attempt to solve a quadratic equation (factorising, use of formula, completing square, or otherwise)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><msup><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>±</mo><msqrt><mn>25</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>24</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;(or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;(or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award the final <em><strong>A1</strong></em> if candidate’s answer includes <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>. Award <em><strong>A0</strong></em> if other incorrect answers are given.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22146755","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ2.2","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Solve 3×9x+5×3x-2=0.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"2","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.7—Solutions of quadratic equations and inequalities, discriminant and nature of roots","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.10—Solving equations graphically and analytically"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}